HEADWORD: Dahoon
<hw>Da*hoon"</hw> <pr>(d⟦adot⟧*h⟦oomac⟧n")</pr>, <ety>[Origin
unknown.]</ety> <def>An evergreen shrub or small tree (<spn>Ilex
cassine</spn>) of the southern United States, bearing red drupes and
having soft, white, close-grained wood; -- called also
<altname><col><b>dahoon holly</b></col></altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
